headline: Why Molina Healthcare (MOH) Stock Is Down Today
summary: Shares of healthcare insurance company Molina Healthcare (NYSE:MOH) fell 14.4% in the afternoon session after the company reported second-quarter earnings that missed analyst expectations and lowered its full-year financial guidance due to rising medical costs. The health insurer's adjusted earnings per share of $5.48 fell short of the $5.62 analyst estimate, driven by margin pressure from higher-than-expected medical expenses.
